Milestones and Final-Stage Chunks

Rule:
- Each chunk reaches FINAL only when implementation, failure mapping, automated validation, and manual validation criteria all exist.
- No chunk is marked FINAL because it "basically works."

Chunk 1: Config and state authority
Scope:
- config.json as the single rules authority
- no conflicting personality/behavior/settings files
- clear split between config, secrets, memory, and ephemeral UI state

Final criteria:
- one authoritative config path for behavior/personality/scene/voice
- state hydration is deterministic
- no settings drift between frontend and backend
- no silent localStorage override of core behavior

Must test:
- backend read/write roundtrip
- migration from legacy config paths
- restart persistence

Chunk 2: Voice session orchestration
Scope:
- mic start/stop
- session lifecycle
- interim/final transcript handling
- processing/replying transitions
- error and restart recovery

Final criteria:
- no stuck listening
- no stuck processing
- no stuck replying
- state transitions always recover cleanly
- reply timing metrics exposed

Must test:
- session start/stop loop
- repeated restart
- forced error recovery
- long idle recovery

Chunk 3: Browser STT primary path
Scope:
- browser speech recognition
- interim transcript display
- final commit behavior
- restart on session end
- echo suppression

Final criteria:
- interim transcript is responsive
- only final transcript enters memory/chat flow
- no self-hearing from TTS in normal operation
- ambient noise is dropped
- weak fragments are ignored

Must test:
- browser speech available
- browser speech unavailable fallback
- TTS active while mic active
- ambient noise phrases
- long sentence commit accuracy

Chunk 4: Local STT fallback
Scope:
- Vosk fallback
- model resolution
- helper script and audio preprocessing
- headless fallback testing

Final criteria:
- fallback activates only when needed
- local STT is measurable and reproducible
- headless smoke exists
- no app hang when fallback is active

Must test:
- headless fallback smoke
- model discovery
- transcription timeout handling
- missing-model failure clarity

Chunk 5: TTS output
Scope:
- edge-tts synthesis
- browser TTS fallback
- playback queueing
- interruption behavior
- speech normalization

Final criteria:
- bot speaks reliably
- bot can be interrupted by user speech
- TTS never wedges the whole session
- no leaked system prompt text is spoken
- speech normalization removes junk formatting

Must test:
- headless TTS smoke
- repeated synth requests
- interrupted playback
- browser fallback

Chunk 6: Self-echo and ambient suppression
Scope:
- TTS suppression window
- bot self-loop prevention
- ambient-noise rejection
- bot-message reingestion prevention

Final criteria:
- bot does not reply to itself
- TTS does not feed back into STT under normal setup
- common ambient phrases never hit memory/chat/LLM

Must test:
- bot speaking while mic active
- delayed echo tail
- Twitch bot-message ignore path
- local bot-response ignore path

Chunk 7: Chat and reply engine
Scope:
- local chat
- Twitch chat
- reply cadence
- command path
- keep-talking mode
- anti-repeat logic

Final criteria:
- controls actually change behavior
- bot does not spam
- keep-talking continues the subject
- question-loop behavior is suppressed
- local vs Twitch posting is explicit and respected

Must test:
- local-only mode
- Twitch-connected but bot-local mode
- cadence changes
- mention reply path
- repeated prompt anti-duplication

Chunk 8: Memory and continuity
Scope:
- salient fact extraction
- pinned memory
- user-specific memory retrieval
- story continuity
- correction precedence

Final criteria:
- names/titles/preferences are retained
- corrections override stale memory
- story continuity survives multiple turns
- memory retrieval is relevant rather than raw-log heavy

Must test:
- repeated recall cases
- contradiction/correction case
- pinned memory precedence
- keep-talking/story continuation case

Chunk 9: Character system
Scope:
- preset characters
- slider tuning
- default voice mapping
- preset packaging

Final criteria:
- character switch updates voice/personality reliably
- presets feel coherent
- no dropdown-style ambiguity
- default voice and style are coupled per character

Must test:
- preset switch persistence
- slider effect persistence
- voice mapping on preset change

Chunk 10: Avatar system
Scope:
- shared embedded renderer
- optional detached shell only if needed later
- rig controls
- jar styling
- lip sync
- path to GPU-backed renderer for higher realism

Final criteria:
- embedded avatar is primary
- no duplicated control surfaces
- rig settings persist
- speech animation plays in embedded runtime
- no separate legacy popup runtime remains active
- renderer abstraction exists so DOM/CSS rig can be replaced by WebGPU / wgpu without changing character data

Must test:
- embedded render
- detach if retained
- rig persistence
- speech animation start/stop
- window/container resizing

Chunk 10A: GPU character renderer
Scope:
- WebGPU / wgpu-backed character stage
- shader lighting
- mesh or quad deformation for mouth, eyes, brows, and head motion
- realistic popout and nested stage parity

Final criteria:
- current avatar data model maps cleanly into the GPU renderer
- nested and detached stages use the same renderer core
- renderer degrades gracefully when WebGPU is unavailable
- realistic motion is materially better than the DOM/CSS fallback

Must test:
- capability detection
- fallback path when GPU is unavailable
- long-session renderer stability
- lip sync and brow sync timing
- consistent render output between nested and detached stages

Chunk 11: Twitch integration
Scope:
- auth sessions
- bot/streamer role separation
- IRC join/send
- EventSub startup
- channel routing

Final criteria:
- role separation is explicit and correct
- bot account is never silently swapped with streamer account
- bot posting toggle is honored
- Twitch disconnect stays disconnected

Must test:
- auth role separation
- connect/disconnect loop
- bot-local mode while connected
- mention reply

Chunk 11A: External live context and Twitch event widgets
Scope:
- backend-owned EventSub/IRC event aggregation
- web search ingestion with timestamps and source metadata
- operator-facing stats/notification/timeline/command-palette widgets
- no raw external event spam into the chat feed

Final criteria:
- external context is source-tagged and time-tagged
- Twitch event widgets are fed by backend events, not frontend guesses
- operator widgets reflect live runtime and stream state accurately
- web search data can be injected later without redesigning the UI or backend model


Chunk 11B: Screen vision observer
Scope:
- backend-owned screen observer subprocess
- screenshot/window capture selection
- sampled frame analysis with local multimodal models
- structured JSON observation events for scene and memory
- no raw caption spam into chat or permanent memory

Final criteria:
- screen analysis never blocks the UI thread
- frame sampling cadence is bounded and configurable
- structured observations are timestamped, source-tagged, and confidence-tagged
- scene layer can consume vision summaries without treating them as direct user speech
- observer can be disabled without affecting local voice or Twitch chat

Must test:
- idle sampling cadence
- active-scene faster cadence
- missing-GPU or missing-model fallback
- observer subprocess crash and restart
- no direct raw-caption posting into chat

Must test:
- EventSub event ingestion
- IRC event aggregation
- notification/timeline rendering from backend payloads
- stale external data rejection
- command palette action dispatch

Chunk 12: Diagnostics and self-test
Scope:
- service health
- voice verification
- self-test
- debug bundle/export

Final criteria:
- diagnostics reflect real runtime state
- warnings are meaningful, not noise
- voice verification can run without launching full UI manually
- failure reasons are actionable

Must test:
- self-test output validity
- voice runtime smoke
- health state transitions

Chunk 13: Headless backend and control plane
Scope:
- backend runtime detached from the UI shell
- optional CLI/daemon execution mode
- local control surface for frontend clients
- backend survives frontend restarts
- child-process supervision for failure isolation

Final criteria:
- core runtime can run without the Tauri window
- the frontend can act as a controller instead of the only runtime shell
- core services can be inspected and controlled headlessly
- voice/status smoke can target the backend directly
- STT/TTS/LLM jobs can be supervised and restarted without killing the parent runtime

Must test:
- headless runtime boot
- prompt via detached runtime
- headless voice smoke via detached runtime
- supervised worker restart/timeout path
- frontend attach/detach
- backend continues running after UI exit
- CLI health/status command path

Chunk 14: Public call link foundation
Scope:
- lightweight public shell
- shared voice-session runtime
- token/config path

Final criteria:
- route separation exists
- public shell does not load owner dashboard
- shared session logic is reused

Must test:
- route load
- voice-session startup on public path

Chunk 15: Performance and anti-freeze
Scope:
- worker-backed hot paths
- bounded concurrency
- minimized rerenders
- runtime timing instrumentation

Final criteria:
- no main-thread churn from transcript flood
- no heavy inactive panel rendering
- no runaway memory growth in normal use
- timing instrumentation exists for STT -> AI -> TTS

Must test:
- sustained mic session
- repeated tab switches
- repeated character changes
- long feed accumulation

